{"title_page": "Bessie Carter", "text_new": "{{Short description|English actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name                 = Bessie Carter\n| birth_name           = Bessie Beatrice Carter\n| birth_place          = [[London]], England\n| birth_date           = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1993|10|25}}\n| occupation           = Actress\n| years_active         = 2006\u2013present\n| television           = ''[[Howards End (miniseries)|Howards End]]'' <br> ''[[Beecham House]]'' <br> ''[[Bridgerton (TV series)|Bridgerton]]''\n| alma mater           = [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gsmd.ac.uk/drama/final_year_actors/graduates_2015_16/bessie_carter/|title=Guildhall School Graduates 2015/2016|website=Guildhall School of Music and Drama}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Bessie Carter''' (born 25 October 1993) is an English actress, known for her role as Evie Wilcox on the [[BBC One|BBC]] television series ''[[Howards End (miniseries)|Howards End]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-01-11/meet-the-cast-of-bbc1-howards-end/|title=Meet the cast of Howards End, 11 January 2019|website=Radio Times}}</ref> (2017) and as Violet Woodhouse on the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] television series [[Beecham House]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2019-07-28/beecham-house-itv-cast-tom-bateman-lesley-nicol-dakota-blue-richards-itv/|title=Meet the cast of ITV\u2019s Indian period drama Beecham House, 28 July 2019|website=Radio Times}}</ref>(2019).\n\n===Early Life===\nCarter was born in [[Westminster]] to actress [[Imelda Staunton]] and actor [[Jim Carter (actor)|Jim Carter]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/go/london/theatre/bessie-carter-takes-after-her-parents-with-new-role-but-says-parents-let-her-do-her-own-thing-a3330311.html|title=Bessie Carter takes after her parents with new role, but says they 'let me do my own thing, 26 August 2016|website=Evening Standard}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/howards-end-bessie-carter-dad-jim-screamed-503597/|title=Howards End\u2019s Bessie Carter, daughter of Downton Abbey star Jim Carter: \u2018Dad screamed when I got the part!\u2019, 14 November 2017|website=what's on tv}}</ref>(2019). She was educated at private school before moving to Camden School for Girls, a state school for the last two years of her secondary education. She studied drama at the [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama]] graduating in 2016 and winning the Spotlight Prize for Best Screen Actor the same year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gsmd.ac.uk/drama/acting_alumni/recent_graduates/bessie_carter_2016/|title=Bessie Carter - Spotlight Prize for Best Screen Actor 2016|website=Guildhall School of Music and Drama}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''\n| Ensemble Factory Woman\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Oil''\n| Sophie\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Good Liar]]''\n| Secretary\n| \n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Two''\n| New Ella\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Emerge''\n| Jess\n| ''Short Film - Post Production''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007-2008\n| ''[[Cranford (TV series)|Cranford]]''\n| Margaret Gidman\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Doc Martin]]''\n| Amy Vincent\n| TV Series - Episode: Farewell My Lovely \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Howards End (miniseries)|Howards End]]''\n| Evie Wilcox\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Beecham House]]''\n| Violet Woodhouse\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Bridgerton (TV series)|Bridgeton]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news