to Camden School for Girls, a state school for the last two years of her secondary education. She studied drama at the [[Guildhall School of Music and Drama]] graduating in 2016 and winning the Spotlight Prize for Best Screen Actor the same year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gsmd.ac.uk/drama/acting_alumni/recent_graduates/bessie_carter_2016/|title=Bessie Carter - Spotlight Prize for Best Screen Actor 2016|website=Guildhall School of Music and Drama}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]''\n| Ensemble Factory Woman\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Oil''\n| Sophie\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Good Liar]]''\n| Secretary\n| \n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Two''\n| New Ella\n| Short Film\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Emerge''\n| Jess\n| ''Short Film - Post Production''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Role\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2007-2008\n| ''[[Cranford (TV series)|Cranford]]''\n| Margaret Gidman\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Doc Martin]]''\n| Amy Vincent\n| TV Series - Episode: Farewell My Lovely \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Howards End (miniseries)|Howards End]]''\n| Evie Wilcox\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Beecham House]]''\n| Violet Woodhouse\n| TV Series\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Bridgerton (TV series)|Bridgeton]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/on-demand/2020-03-25/bridgerton-netflix/|title=When is Bridgerton released on Netflix? What\u2019s it about?, 25 March 2020|website=Radio Times}}</ref> \n| Prudence Featherington\n| TV Series\n|-\n|}\n\n===Theatre===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Year\n!style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Title\n!style